    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-01-22T15:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-01-22T15:00:00-05:00" n="299"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d299">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/1–2149: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stuart</hi>
                    </persName>)<note n="33" xml:id="d299fn33">Repeated to the Consul General at
                        Taipei as No. 5.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-01-22T15:00:00-05:00"
                            >January 22, 1949—3 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>84. Dept would appreciate your obtaining from JUSMAG<note n="34"
                        xml:id="d299fn34">Joint U.S. Military Advisory Group.</note> (your 183 Jan
                        21<note n="35" xml:id="d299fn35">
                        <ref target="frus1949v08#ch1">Vol. <hi rend="smallcaps">viii</hi>,
                            “Political and military situation in China”, chapter I</ref>.</note>)
                    more detailed info, re disposition US milit equipment landed Formosa.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
